BY REPRESENTATIVE OWEN
ENERGY: Requests a review of the Climate Initiatives Task Force and the Louisiana
Climate Action Plan by the House Committee on Natural Resources and
Environment
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To authorize and request the House Committee on Natural Resources and Environment to
3 conduct a hearing to review the Louisiana Climate Action Plan of 2022, including
4 the resulting Priority Climate Action Plan, created by the Climate Initiatives Task
5 Force.
6 WHEREAS, in August of 2020 Governor John Bel Edwards issued an executive
7 order to create a Climate Initiatives Task Force whom he charged with developing a
8 statewide comprehensive climate action plan as a framework for future policy initiatives;
9 and
10 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Climate Action Plan, submitted in February of 2022 by
11 the Climate Initiatives Task Force pursuant to Executive Order JBE 2020-18, promoted a
12 net-zero greenhouse gas emissions goal by 2050, which aligned with international agendas
13 like the Paris Climate Agreement; and
14 WHEREAS, committees of neither chamber of the Legislature of Louisiana
15 conducted a formal review or oversight hearing on the plan or its implications; and
16 WHEREAS, in 2024 and 2025 new administrations were sworn in both the state of
17 Louisiana and the United States federal government that shifted policy initiatives toward the
18 principles of limited government, free markets, individual liberty, energy dominance, and
19 American sovereignty; and
