1 WHEREAS, it is now in the best interest of the citizens of Louisiana to conduct a
2 thorough, independent review of the Climate Initiatives Task Force and the 2022 Louisiana
3 Climate Action Plan to determine their ongoing need, applicability, or non-applicability; and
4 WHEREAS, the objective of the review shall be to assess current environmental,
5 ecological, and natural resource priorities in Louisiana in the context of long-term energy
6 dominance and economic strength and to ensure their congruence with national objectives
7 such as withdrawing from the Paris Climate Accords and any other treaties or agreements
8 that are antithetical to American values and sovereignty; and
9 WHEREAS, good stewardship of Louisiana's natural resources, including our air,
10 land and soil, and subsurface resources should be a primary focus during the review; and
11 WHEREAS, the ultimate objective of the review shall be to determine how much of
12 the 2022 Climate Action Plan should be publicly repudiated and which provisions, if any,
13 should be retained or adapted; and
14 WHEREAS, the review shall also include an investigation and determination of
15 whether any foreign or malign influences or actors from adversary nations were involved in
16 the creation of the 2022 Climate Action Plan; and
17 WHEREAS, Louisiana's economy is deeply rooted in the energy, petrochemical,
18 manufacturing, agriculture, and transportation sectors, which provide substantial
19 employment, tax revenue, and economic stability to the citizens of this state; and
20 WHEREAS, embracing America-first and Louisiana-first policies focused on
21 unleashing domestic oil and gas production, protecting private property rights, reducing
22 dependence on the federal government, and promoting free-market innovation will better
23 serve the state's economy, workers, and citizens.
24 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
25 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby authorize and request the House Committee on Natural
26 Resources and Environment to conduct a hearing to review the Louisiana Climate Action
27 Plan of 2022, including the resulting Priority Climate Action Plan, developed by the Climate
28 Initiatives Task Force.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the chairman of the House Committee on
30 Natural Resources and Environment may request input from the Department of Conservation
